Hundreds of striking lecturers yesterday held a peaceful demonstration on the streets of Eldoret town. The lecturers from the University of Eldoret and Moi University first met at Moi University&rsquo;s town campus.They later addressed a press conference at Moi University&rsquo;s school of medicine. Waving placards, the lecturers blamed the government for their continued suffering, saying they will not relent in their fight for a pay increase.Moi University&rsquo;s Academic Staff Union secretary general Jack Okumu said they will not be cowed by threats from the judiciary. &ldquo;We know the government has resolved to use the judicial system to harass us on several occasions. It is now six years since we last negotiated a salary increase. What we are asking for is not beyond the means of this country,&rdquo; he said.